sources.title: Too Much Beef (1936) REX BELL
sources.description:
FIRST TIME on YouTUBE!
Stars: Rex Bell, Constance Bergen, Forrest Taylor
Director: Harry L. Fraser

Someone is adding beef to Rocky Brown's herd and changing the brands to make it look like he is rustling.

TRIVIA: Cowboy actor Rex Bell was born on October 16, 1903 in Chicago, Illinois. He was married to Clara Bow until his death on July 4, 1962 in Las Vegas, Nevada.

metadata.Plot: Someone is adding beef to Rocky Brown's herds and changing the brands to make it look like he is rustling. Then he is framed for murder and jailed. Johnny Argyle who has been sent to investigate believes he is innocent and sets out to prove it and starts with hides that have been rebranded.
metadata.Writer: William Colt MacDonald, Robert F. Hill
metadata.Actors: Rex Bell, Constance Bergen, Forrest Taylor
